data.description: Welcome to The Olde Glencove Hotel nestled above a quiet cove on Puget Sound. Built as a resort hotel in 1896 it has been a National Registered Historic Place since 1978. This Classic Victorian Building has been beautifully restored by the Nadeau family which decided to open for weddings, tours, and as a Bed & Breakfast. Today it sits on about 1 acre of land and boasts Formal Dining, Living & Entertaining spaces on the main plus a half bath. The second floor has 3 bedrooms & Office/bedroom, a 3/4 bath & 1/2 bath as well as a veranda to take in the views at the end of the hall. A separate 2-story MIL/apartment with a kitchenette & 2 baths is a win. With over 3,338 Sq Ft of potential overlooking the Sound.
